name: victor Wilson
text: I love this place! Good price great people.

name: john hamilton
text: Great family friendly swim club not too expensive to join either. they have a snack bar and a diving board. They have a kiddie pool and a deck with tons of shade it is kind of old school like something from leave it to Beaver but it is super awesome.

name: Shelby Gillroy
text: This pool looks nice and whoever goes inside probably enjoys it. I'm sure the staff works hard to keep the pool nice. Unfortunately, this is not a public pool like Google lists. This pool is private. A lady told me on the phone that I could come to the pool as long as I paid two dollars since I'm not a member. I drove twenty miles here thinking I would get to enjoy the water when I came. I was told by one of the staff that only people who are members get to come to the pool and their guests when I tried to give them the two dollars I had. I left upset that I was told one thing on the phone and given a completely different story when I got there.

name: Joel Reimer (JWR1)
text: Through my wife our family is second gen Gator's. We are in our 12th+ year now. It is so well run by Ms. Velda and her fabulous life guard team. It is so convenient for MIDtown to Downtown folks. Come by and check it out.

name: Paul Baldwin
text: Great family environment for summer fun. Pool staff works hard to make sure everyone has an enjoyable time. Grills and picnic tables available to bring your lunch and stay all day. Facilities are always clean. Fun activities throughout the summer like movie nights and special fun on holidays. Membership is low cost.

resp.text: Thank you Paul for the kind words. Its almost that time of year again. Getting excited.

name: Karis W
text: This is such a nice pool. We came here as a guest with a friend of mine and had a wonderful time. The atmosphere is really cheerful and family-friendly and it's very well maintained. I even met the owners while we were there and they were super nice people. We are hoping to join next summer! My only qualm is that there is no diaper changing station. I would love to see them add one.
